Markets: drive "My Trade" column from real orders, not a backtest

The previous "Strategy" column ran a live backtest of the active profile
and showed hypothetical Won/Lost outcomes that were wrong and confusing
(it claimed fills on markets the rules never matched, and plotted bogus
markers). Rip all of that out.

The column is now "My Trade": for each market it folds the user's actual
entry orders into a factual status - Won / Lost (settled), Open (filled,
unresolved), or Resting (placed, unfilled), with a dash when there was no
trade. Hover shows the side and net P&L. The price chart keeps showing the
real order markers it always did.

